Usage of airfi infrastructure:
==============================
1.
install following packages:
moreutils
libcurl4-openssl-dev
nlohmann-json3-dev

2.
when device boots for the first time, create folder in /var/log/ with
right ownership and permissions for logs

/usr/local/bin	=> airfi_log_setup.sh
/etc/system/system => airfi-log-perms.service
systemctl enable airfi-log-perms.service (for enabling and link file creation)

this will run onetime

3.
log dmesg in /var/log/dmesg_logs every 10 minutes from device boot as seperate files
create folder in /var/log/ with right ownership and permissions for logs

/usr/local/bin  => log_dmesg.sh
/etc/system/system => log-dmesg.service
/etc/system/system => log-dmesg.timer (run every 10 min)

systemctl enable --now log-dmesg.timer (for enabling and link file creation)

4.
/home/open/old_deploy/yolov8_multhreading_Airfi/install/rknn_yolov8_demo_Linux/airfi_data => airfi_data 

airfi_data:
IN (0 - default)
OUT (0 - default)
CAMERA STATUS (1 - default meaning connected)

service and timers chaining:
----------------------------

boot => airfi-log-perms.service => airfi.service => .......

every day at 1700 hrs:

daily_shutdown.timer
	=> daily_shutdown.service
		=> stops airfi
		=> starts airfi_count_reset.service (reset count)
		=> starts airfi-restart.timer
			=> airfi-restart.service with 2min delay


/usr/local/bin 	=> airfi_launch.sh
/usr/local/bin  => airfi-count-reset(airfi-count-reset.cpp)
		   aarch64-linux-gnu-g++ airfi-count-reset.cpp -o airfi-count-reset
/etc/system/system => airfi_count_reset.service

/etc/system/system => daily_shutdown.timer
/etc/system/system => daily_shutdown.service
/etc/system/system => airfi.service
/etc/system/system => airfi-restart.timer
/etc/system/system => airfi-restart.service

systemctl enable airfi.service(for enabling and link file creation)
systemctl enable --now daily_shutdown.timer

notes:
------
move airfi_data(from existing location) to /etc/airfi/*

5.
daily_shutdown.service
device_payload.service
device_health.cpp
json.hpp

/usr/local/bin  => device_health
		   (aarch64-linux-gnu-g++ device_health.cpp -o device_health -lcurl -lsqlite3 -lpthread)

/etc/system/system => device_payload.service
systemctl enable device_payload.service(for enabling and link file creation)

6.
airfi_payload.service
airfiDataInsert.cpp

/usr/local/bin  => airfiDataInsert
                   (aarch64-linux-gnu-g++ airfiDataInsert.cpp -o airfiDataInsert -lcurl -lsqlite3 -lpthread)

/etc/system/system => airfi_payload.service
systemctl enable airfi_payload.service(for enabling and link file creation)
